ungen.Der Band ist Hanns Christof Brennecke zum 70. Geburtstag gewidmet.   aThe Imperium Romanum was marked by a diverse and differentiated history of reciprocal interaction with the church and theology. The study examines this ever-changing relationship, encompassing a broad time span from the first to the sixth century. The essays include both the Eastern and Western parts of the Imperium and its successor states, and explore the theme by drawing from a wide range of literary genres.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aChurch and stateyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 0aChurch and statezByzantine EmpirexHistory. 0aChurch and statezRomexHistory. 0aChurch historyyPrimitive and early church, ca. 30-600. 4aAntike. 4aKirchengeschichte. 4aNeues Testament. 4aNew Testament. 4aTheologie. 4aantiquity. 4achurch history. 4atheology. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh1 aHeil, Uta, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUlrich, Jörg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2017z9783110548259oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831105272090 cprintz978311052711740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311052791940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110527919423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110527919.jpg  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017